# Implementation Plan - Flutter JS Bridge

This plan outlines the integration of a production-ready JavaScript bridge to communicate between the React web app and the Flutter InAppWebView wrapper. This will provide a more stable and extensible way to access native features like the camera.

## Proposed Changes

### [Frontend Utilities]
#### [NEW] [flutterBridge.js](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/Homster/Frontend/src/utils/flutterBridge.js)
Create a singleton utility class to handle:
- Detecting the Flutter environment.
- Providing a promise-based `waitForFlutter` listener.
- Generic `callHandler` for arbitrary native calls.
- Specific `openCamera` wrapper that returns a standard [File](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/Homster/Frontend/src/modules/vendor/components/common/ImageUploader.jsx#15-62) object from Base64 data.

### [Frontend Components]

#### [MODIFY] [WorkCompletionModal.jsx](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/Homster/Frontend/src/modules/worker/components/common/WorkCompletionModal.jsx)
- Import `flutterBridge`.
- Replace direct `<input type="file" />` behavior with a `handleNativeCamera` trigger.

#### [MODIFY] [ImageUploader.jsx](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/Homster/Frontend/src/modules/vendor/components/common/ImageUploader.jsx)
- Import `flutterBridge`.
- Add a toggle for Native Camera in the upload UI if in Flutter environment.
- Use `flutterBridge.openCamera()` to get standard [File](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/Homster/Frontend/src/modules/vendor/components/common/ImageUploader.jsx#15-62) objects.

#### [MODIFY] [BookingDetails/index.jsx](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/Homster/Frontend/src/modules/vendor/pages/BookingDetails/index.jsx) (Audit)
- Review any native-like triggers (e.g., location tracking enhancements) to see if they should move to the bridge pattern.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Flutter-Side Requirements**:
> For this bridge to work, the Flutter developer MUST implement the following:
> 1. **JavaScript Handler**: Register `openCamera` in the `InAppWebViewController`.
> 2. **Ready Event**: Dispatch `flutterInAppWebViewPlatformReady` in the `onLoadStop` callback.
> 3. **Base64 Response**: Ensure the native `openCamera` returns a JSON object with `success`, `mimeType`, `base64`, and `fileName`.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- **Browser Testing**: Ensure the app continues to work in standard Chrome/Edge (fallback to standard file input).
- **Flutter Testing**: (To be performed by the user) Verify that clicking "Add / Cam" successfully opens the native camera and returns the image as a preview in the modal.
